name: Liz Cheney
summary: In the aftermath of the January 6th, 2021, Capitol riot, the House Republican Party has released a report and made recommendations regarding the actions of Republican Congresswoman Liz Cheney, who serves on the January 6th Committee. The report calls for a criminal investigation into Cheney, alleging that she engaged in witness tampering and other improper conduct. The Republican Party's actions have drawn criticism from Democrats and some Republicans, who view it as an attempt to retaliate against Cheney for her role in investigating the riot and holding former President Trump accountable. The FBI has not yet announced whether it will open an investigation into Cheney, and the full extent of the House Republican Party's recommendations remains unclear.

name: Elton John
summary: Elton John's life and career are explored in depth in a new documentary streaming on Disney+. The film covers his music, drug use, relationship with John Lennon, and family life. In an interview, John revealed that he wants his gravestone to bear the phrase "That's all that counts," which he believes reflects his values and his legacy. He also hopes to be remembered for his contributions to music and his advocacy work, including his support for LGBTQ+ rights and HIV/AIDS awareness. The documentary is available for streaming on Disney+, TheWrap, and Variety. Despite being known for his support of substance use recovery, John has recently expressed concern about the legalization of marijuana, calling it "one of the greatest mistakes of all time." The film also features interviews with musicians Billie Eilish, Brandi Carlile, and Dua Lipa, who discuss their collaborations and relationships with John.

name: FOMC
summary: The Federal Reserve (Fed) has implemented another interest rate cut, this time by a quarter point, indicating only two more reductions in 2025. Despite this action, Fed Chair Jerome Powell maintains that the economy is in a "really good place." While the Fed acknowledges that inflation is below target, it believes the economy is still at risk of overheating. As a result, the Fed has signaled that future cuts will be more gradual and less frequent. Market reactions have been mixed, with stocks initially declining before trading mixed ahead of the Fed's decision. The impact on the US dollar is also being closely watched.
